verbose_text: Minimally adjusted Cox proportional hazards models including triglyceride, LDL, and HDL levels continued to demonstrate a stepwise association between triglycerides and LEA risk : 150-199 mg/dL, HR 1.07 (95% CI 0.89-1.29); 200-499 mg/dL, 1.20 (1.03-1.40); and> 500 mg/dL, 1.39 (1.03-1.88) (reference < 150 mg/dL).
